00:37:45.080 --> 00:37:46.380
&gt;&gt; Kristin Ann Hass: I
would just add quickly

00:37:46.380 --> 00:37:47.680
that it's important to remember

00:37:47.680 --> 00:37:50.330
that memorials are
fairly blunt instruments.

00:37:50.330 --> 00:37:53.120
And they are used as such.

00:37:53.120 --> 00:37:55.990
And that we don't need
to hold onto memorials

00:37:55.990 --> 00:37:57.860
as the keepers of our history.

00:37:57.860 --> 00:38:02.460
That's why historians
spend years and hours

00:38:02.460 --> 00:38:04.170
in the archives, right?

00:38:04.170 --> 00:38:06.900
There are more subtle
and more complicated ways

00:38:06.900 --> 00:38:08.810
to tell history.

00:38:08.810 --> 00:38:12.460
And the reason that people want
these memorials to come down is

00:38:12.460 --> 00:38:16.360
because they are successfully
doing the work that the people

00:38:16.360 --> 00:38:19.650
that erected them wanted done.

00:38:19.650 --> 00:38:23.450
And so they're working
and that's a problem.

00:38:23.450 --> 00:38:27.400
Because of the reasons they
wanted them to be built.

