00:38:35.710 --> 00:38:37.990
like to offer my comment on one

00:38:37.990 --> 00:38:40.600
of the first Civil
War Memorials,

00:38:40.600 --> 00:38:43.170
which is the Statue of Liberty.

00:38:43.170 --> 00:38:45.910
Now most people, and this
is what's fascinating to me

00:38:45.910 --> 00:38:49.080
about how memorials
change in their concept,

00:38:49.080 --> 00:38:53.840
the French when they wanted
to gift the Statue of Liberty

00:38:53.840 --> 00:38:56.900
to the US, it was to
celebrate the preservation

00:38:56.900 --> 00:38:58.210
of the republic.

00:38:58.210 --> 00:39:01.680
The preservation of democracy
and the abolition of slavery.

00:39:01.680 --> 00:39:04.700
And if you look carefully at
the statue of liberty and look

00:39:04.700 --> 00:39:08.570
at her ankles, there's a
broken chain on her ankle.

00:39:08.570 --> 00:39:11.690
That was a symbol of the
abolition of slavery.

00:39:11.690 --> 00:39:16.950
However, from the late 1860's
when the statue was conceived,

00:39:16.950 --> 00:39:21.890
to 1886 when it was finally
dedicated, America had changed,

00:39:21.890 --> 00:39:26.720
immigration had become a
much more important issue,

00:39:26.720 --> 00:39:29.400
and the Statue of
Liberty became associated

00:39:29.400 --> 00:39:32.480
with welcoming immigrants
to America.

00:39:32.480 --> 00:39:36.570
Emma Lazarus's poem, which was
written as part of a fundraiser

00:39:36.570 --> 00:39:40.140
for the pedestal of the statue,
wasn't placed on the statue

00:39:40.140 --> 00:39:44.000
until the early 20th century
but it was a well-known poem

00:39:44.000 --> 00:39:48.290
and really transformed the
statue from a preserving our,

00:39:48.290 --> 00:39:50.870
the preservation of
American democracy

00:39:50.870 --> 00:39:56.190
to welcoming immigrants to
the country and a symbol

00:39:56.190 --> 00:39:58.840
of immigrant, the
value of contribution

00:39:58.840 --> 00:40:00.340
of immigrants to our country.

00:40:00.340 --> 00:40:03.360
Now, audience, please.

00:40:03.360 --> 00:40:04.880
&gt;&gt; Thank you, and thank
